description: This file defines a data model for movie scripts using Pydantic, and sets up an agent that generates movie scripts with a specific Gemini model. It also demonstrates invoking the agent to produce a response.

classes.name: MovieScript
classes.description: A Pydantic model representing the structure of a movie script, including setting, ending, genre, name, characters, storyline, and rating.

methods.name: print_response
methods.description: Method of the Agent class used to generate and print a response based on a prompt.
